  "source_data_quality_note": "Source MD is widefield-fluorescence template (fan-out artifact). Physics below is grounded in Kerbl et al. 2023 3DGS and follow-up work (Mip-Splatting, 2DGS, SuGaR).",
  "E": {
    "description": "3DGS represents a scene as a set of N anisotropic 3D Gaussians parameterised by center mu_i, covariance Sigma_i, RGB color c_i (or spherical-harmonic coefficients), and opacity alpha_i. Rendering projects each Gaussian onto the image plane as a 2D Gaussian, sorts by depth, and alpha-composites per pixel. The explicit primitive set supports real-time rasterization and direct differentiation.",
    "forward_model": "C(r) = sum_{i=1}^{N_visible} T_i * alpha_i_2d * c_i,  T_i = prod_{j<i} (1 - alpha_j_2d),  alpha_i_2d = alpha_i * exp(-0.5 (r - mu_proj_i)^T Sigma_proj_i^{-1} (r - mu_proj_i))",
    "world_state_x": "Set of N 3D Gaussians: (mu_i in R^3, Sigma_i in PSD^{3x3}, c_i in R^{3 * L_SH}, alpha_i in [0, 1]) for i = 1..N",
    "observation_y": "K posed reference images {I_k, T_k}_{k=1..K}",
    "physical_parameters_theta": [
      "Number of Gaussians N (typically 100k-5M)",
      "Spherical-harmonic degree L_SH for view-dependent color",
